e-tune LLMs on domain-specific data.\n\n2. **Secure Data Handling:**\n   - Implement advanced encryption techniques and secure data handling practices to protect confidential information.\n   - Develop synthetic data generation methods to train LLMs without using real, sensitive data.\n\n3. **Multimodal Data Processing:**\n   - Create multimodal LLM architectures that can effectively process and correlate text, images, and other data types.\n   - Develop pretraining methods that leverage large-scale multimodal datasets.\n\n4. **Regulatory Compliance:**\n   - Design LLMs with built-in compliance checks to ensure adherence to legal and regulatory requirements.\n   - Develop explainable AI techniques to provide transparent and interpretable outputs from LLMs.\n\n### Summarization\n\nThe key gaps identified in the introduction revolve around integrating professional expertise, handling confidential data securely, processing multimodal documents, and ensuring regulatory compliance. Potential research ideas include developing frameworks for knowledge integration, secure data handling techniques, multimodal LLM architectures, and compliance-focused LLM designs.\n\n### Formulate a New Research Idea\n\n**High-level summarized insight of the research field:**\nThe integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains such as finance, healthcare, and law presents significant opportunities and challenges. While LLMs have the potential to revolutionize these fields, they require robust methods for handling professional expertise, confidential data, multimodal documents, and regulatory compliance.\n\n**Here are the five core questions:**\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nHow can large language models be effectively integrated with professional expertise in critical domains like finance, healthcare, and law while ensuring secure handling of confidential data and compliance with legal regulations?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nSolving this problem is crucial for advancing the practical applications of LLMs in critical societal domains. It will enable LLMs to provide reliable, secure, and compliant solutions, enhancing decision-making processes and improving outcomes in finance, healthcare, and law.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe challenges include effectively integrating domain-specific knowledge, securely handling confidential data, processing complex multimodal documents, and ensuring compliance with legal regulations. Naive approaches may fail due to the complexity and sensitivity of the data involved.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has not fully addressed the integration of professional expertise, secure data handling, multimodal data processing, and regulatory compliance in a unified framework. Existing solutions often focus on individual aspects of the problem, lacking a comprehensive approach.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed approach involves developing a unified framework that integrates professional expertise through knowledge graphs, ensures secure data handling using advanced encryption techniques, processes multimodal data using innovative LLM architectures, and incorporates compliance checks. The expected outcomes include a robust LLM capable of providing reliable, secure, and compliant solutions in critical domains."}

