al, theoretical, or practical obstacles that need to be overcome. MAKE IT CLEAR.\n\n               **[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\n\n               Identify gaps or limitations in previous research or existing solutions.\n               Discuss any barriers that have prevented this problem from being solved until now.\n               Explain how your approach differs from or improves upon prior work. MAKE IT CLEAR.\n\n               **[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\n\n               Outline your proposed methodology in detail, including the method, dataset, and metrics that you plan to use.\n               Describe the expected outcomes. MAKE IT CLEAR.\n\n            Please work together to produce the '5q' for your proposed research idea.\n\n            Good luck!\n            ", 'agent7': "\n            Dear Research Team,\n\n            You are collaborating to generate a new research idea based on the following Introduction:\n\n            **Introduction**\n\n             Introduction\nThe advent of large language models (LLMs) such as ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2022) and GPT-4 (OpenAI, 2023)\nmarks a significant milestone in the evolution of artificial intelligence. The research integrating LLMs with\nvarious disciplines, i.e., LLM+X, such as math, science, finance, healthcare, law, etc., is starting as a new\nepoch powered by collaborative endeavors spanning diverse communities. In this survey paper, we offer an\nexploration of the methodologies, applications, challenges, ethics, and future opportunities of LLMs within\ncritical societal domains , including finance, healthcare , andlaw. These domains are major cornerstones\nof societal function and well-being, each playing a critical role in the fabric of daily life and the broader\neconomic and social systems. They are frequently discussed together due to shared characteristics, including\nthereliance on extensive professional expertise ,highly confidential data ,extensive multimodal documents ,high\nlegal risk and strict regulations , and the requirement for explainability and fairness.\nReliance on Professional Expertise. These domains require extensive professional knowledge and\nexperience. The finance domain involves complex financial analysis, investment strategies, and economic\nforecasting, necessitating deep knowledge of financial theories, market behavior, and fiscal policy (Benninga,\n2014; Fridson & Alvarez, 2022; Roberts, 1959; Geels, 2013; Franses, 1998; Easterly & Rebelo, 1993). Healthcare\nrequires specialized knowledge in medical sciences, patient care, diagnostics, and treatment planning, and\nprofessionals are trained for years in their specific fields (Melnick et al., 2002; Gowda et al., 2014; P. Collins,\n1998; Brauer & Ferguson, 2015; Thomas et al., 2022). The legal domain demands a thorough understanding\nof legal principles, statutes, case law, and judicial procedures, with practitioners spending extensive periods\nin legal education and training (Hart & Green, 2012; Dworkin, 1986; Sunstein, 2018; Epstein & Sharkey, 2020;\nFriedman, 2005; Chemerinsky, 2023; MacCormick, 1994).The need for profound professional expertise in these\ndomains presents significant challenges in equipping LLMs with the requisite knowledge and capabilities (Li\net al., 2023d; Xie et al., 2024b; Islam et al., 2023; Nori et al., 2023a;b; Tan et al., 2023; Yu et al., 2022; Choi\net al., 2021; Iu & Wong, 2023).\nHighly Confidential Data. Unlike many other domains where data might be more public or less sensitive,\nfinance, healthcare, and law deal with information that is mostly personal and confidential. This brings\nunique challenges for LLM-based research, which is essentially data-driven. LLMs must be trained and tested\nin a manner that prevents data breaches or inadvertent disclosures. This necessitates research challenges\nsuch as training data synthesis, encryption techniques, secure data handling practices, transfer learning, etc.\nExtensive Multimodal Documents. The complexity and multimodal nature of documents in these\nsectors mark another unique challenge. Financial documents may contain not only text but also tables\nand charts in diverse structures (Chen et al., 2021b; Bhatia et al., 2024). Healthcare data may contain\ntext and various medical imaging modalities Gee et al. (2004); Wood et al. (2020); Yan et al. (2023c),\nsuch as X-ray Radiography, Ultrasound, Computed Tomography (CT) and Magnetic Resonance Imaging\n(MRI). Legal documents may contain text, images of evidence, audio recordings of testimonies, or video\ndepositions (Matoesian & Gilbert, 2018; He et al., 2023a). Developing LLMs that can accurately interpret\nand correlate information across modalities is crucial, demanding innovative approaches to model architecture\nand data processing.\nHigh Legal Risk and Strict Regulations. Considering the potential serious consequences of actions\nin finance, healthcare, and law,\n\n            **Your Task**\n\n            Use only the Introduction above as your literature context. External paper databases, arXiv, author-profile APIs, and web search are not part of this benchmark.\n\n            1. **Context analysis**: Summarize the problem setting, prior approaches mentioned in the Introduction, and implied gaps you can infer from that text alone.\n\n            2. **Brainstorming**: Collaboratively brainstorm potential research ideas that build upon or address gaps in the Introduction.\n\n            3. **Summarization**: Summarize your collective ideas.\n\n            4. **Formulate a New Research Idea**: Develop a new research proposal in the format of the '5q', defined below:\n\n               **Here is a high-level summarized insight of a research field Machine Learning.**\n\n               **Here are the five core questions:**\n\n               **[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\n\n               Formulate the specific research question you aim to address. Only output one question and do not include any more information.\n\n               **[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\n\n               Explain the broader implications of solving this problem for the research community.\n               Discuss how such a paper will affect future research.\n               Discuss how addressing this question could advance knowledge or lead to practical applications.\n\n               **[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\n\n               Discuss the challenges and complexities involved in solving this problem.\n               Explain why naive or straightforward approaches may fail.\n               Identify any technical, theoretical, or practical obstacles that need to be overcome. MAKE IT CLEAR.\n\n               **[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\n\n               Identify gaps or limitations in previous research or existing solutions.\n               Discuss any barriers that have prevented this problem from being solved until now.\n               Explain how your approach differs from or improves upon prior work. MAKE IT CLEAR.\n\n               **[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\n\n               Outline your proposed methodology in detail, including the method, dataset, and metrics that you plan to use.\n               Describe the expected outcomes. MAKE IT CLEAR.\n\n            Please work together to produce the '5q' for your proposed research idea.\n\n            Good luck!\n            "}, 'task_results': [{'agent_id': 'agent1', 'result': "Result from the model:### Context Analysis\n\n**Problem Setting:**\nThe introduction discusses the integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains such as finance, healthcare, and law. The key challenges include the need for profound professional expertise, handling highly confidential data, processing extensive multimodal documents, and adhering to high legal risk and strict regulations.\n\n**Prior Approaches:**\n- **Professional Expertise:** The introduction mentions the need for equipping LLMs with the requisite knowledge and capabilities, but does not detail specific methods or solutions.\n- **Confidential Data:** Challenges such as training data synthesis, encryption techniques, secure data handling practices, and transfer learning are acknowledged but not elaborated upon.\n- **Multimodal Documents:** The complexity and multimodal nature of documents in these sectors are recognized, but no specific solutions are provided.\n- **Legal Risk and Regulations:** The importance of explainability and fairness is highlighted, but no specific methodologies are discussed.\n\n**Implied Gaps:**\n- **Knowledge Integration:** There is a gap in how LLMs can effectively integrate and utilize professional expertise.\n- **Data Security:** Methods for secure handling and training of LLMs on confidential data are not well-addressed.\n- **Multimodal Processing:** Innovative approaches to processing and correlating information across different modalities are needed.\n- **Explainability and Fairness:** Techniques for ensuring that LLMs are explainable and fair in their outputs are not thoroughly explored.\n\n### Brainstorming\n\n1. **Knowledge Integration:**\n   - Develop a framework for integrating professional expertise into LLMs through domain-specific training and knowledge transfer techniques.\n   - Create a system that allows LLMs to consult and update their knowledge base with domain experts in real-time.\n\n2. **Data Security:**\n   - Design secure data handling practices and encryption techniques specifically tailored for LLM training and inference.\n   - Explore the use of synthetic data generation to reduce reliance on real, confidential data.\n\n3. **Multimodal Processing:**\n   - Develop multimodal LLM architectures that can effectively process and correlate information across different data types.\n   - Create tools for automatic extraction and integration of information from diverse document types.\n\n4. **Explainability and Fairness:**\n   - Implement explainability techniques that allow users to understand the reasoning behind LLM outputs.\n   - Develop fairness-aware training methods to ensure that LLMs do not perpetuate biases present in training data.\n\n### Summarization\n\nThe collective ideas focus on addressing the key challenges in integrating LLMs with critical societal domains. These include developing methods for knowledge integration, ensuring data security, processing multimodal documents, and enhancing explainability and fairness.\n\n### Formulate a New Research Idea\n\n**High-level summarized insight of a research field Machine Learning:**\nLLMs have the potential to revolutionize critical societal domains by integrating professional expertise, handling confidential data securely, processing multimodal documents, and ensuring explainability and fairness.\n\n**Here are the five core questions:**\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nHow can LLMs be effectively integrated with professional expertise in critical domains like finance, healthcare, and law while ensuring data security, multimodal document processing, and fairness?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nSolving this problem will enable LLMs to be more widely adopted in critical domains, improving decision-making processes, enhancing efficiency, and ensuring that AI systems are trustworthy and fair. This research will have significant implications for the future of AI in society.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe challenges include the need for specialized knowledge integration, secure data handling, effective multimodal processing, and ensuring fairness. Naive approaches may fail due to the complexity of these domains and the need for robust, scalable solutions.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has not fully addressed the integration of professional expertise, secure data handling, multimodal document processing, and fairness in a unified framework. Existing solutions are often domain-specific and lack the scalability and robustness required for widespread adoption.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed approach includes:\n- Developing a domain-specific knowledge integration framework.\n- Implementing secure data handling practices and synthetic data generation techniques.\n- Creating multimodal LLM architectures for effective document processing.\n- Incorporating explainability and fairness-aware training methods.\n- Evaluating the proposed framework on real-world datasets from finance, healthcare, and law.\n- Expected outcomes include improved decision-making processes, enhanced efficiency, and increased trust in AI systems.\n"}, {'agent_id': 'agent2', 'result': "Result from the model:### Context Analysis\n\n**Problem Setting:**\nThe introduction discusses the integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains such as finance, healthcare, and law. The focus is on the methodologies, applications, challenges, ethics, and future opportunities of LLMs in these domains. Key challenges include the need for professional expertise, handling of highly confidential data, processing of extensive multimodal documents, and adhering to high legal risk and strict regulations.\n\n**Prior Approaches:**\n- **Professional Expertise:** The introduction mentions the need for deep knowledge in specific fields, but does not detail specific approaches to integrating this expertise into LLMs.\n- **Confidential Data:** Challenges related to data breaches and secure handling are acknowledged, but no specific solutions are mentioned.\n- **Multimodal Documents:** The complexity of multimodal data is recognized, but no specific methods for processing and correlating this data are discussed.\n- **Legal Risk and Regulations:** The importance of compliance is highlighted, but no specific strategies for ensuring adherence to regulations are provided.\n\n**Implied Gaps:**\n- **Integration of Professional Expertise:** There is a need for methods to effectively integrate domain-specific knowledge into LLMs.\n- **Secure Data Handling:** Solutions for secure training and testing of LLMs with confidential data are lacking.\n- **Multimodal Data Processing:** Innovative approaches to processing and correlating multimodal data are required.\n- **Regulatory Compliance:** Strategies for ensuring that LLMs comply with legal and regulatory requirements are needed.\n\n### Brainstorming\n\n1. **Integration of Professional Expertise:**\n   - Develop a framework for incorporating domain-specific knowledge into LLMs through knowledge graphs or expert-curated datasets.\n   - Use transfer learning techniques to fine-tune LLMs on domain-specific data.\n\n2. **Secure Data Handling:**\n   - Implement advanced encryption techniques and secure data handling practices to protect confidential information.\n   - Develop synthetic data generation methods to train LLMs without using real, sensitive data.\n\n3. **Multimodal Data Processing:**\n   - Create multimodal LLM architectures that can effectively process and correlate text, images, and other data types.\n   - Develop pretraining methods that leverage large-scale multimodal datasets.\n\n4. **Regulatory Compliance:**\n   - Design LLMs with built-in compliance checks to ensure adherence to legal and regulatory requirements.\n   - Develop explainable AI techniques to provide transparent and interpretable outputs from LLMs.\n\n### Summarization\n\nThe key gaps identified in the introduction revolve around integrating professional expertise, handling confidential data securely, processing multimodal documents, and ensuring regulatory compliance. Potential research ideas include developing frameworks for knowledge integration, secure data handling techniques, multimodal LLM architectures, and compliance-focused LLM designs.\n\n### Formulate a New Research Idea\n\n**High-level summarized insight of the research field:**\nThe integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains such as finance, healthcare, and law presents significant opportunities and challenges. While LLMs have the potential to revolutionize these fields, they require robust methods for handling professional expertise, confidential data, multimodal documents, and regulatory compliance.\n\n**Here are the five core questions:**\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nHow can large language models be effectively integrated with professional expertise in critical domains like finance, healthcare, and law while ensuring secure handling of confidential data and compliance with legal regulations?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nSolving this problem is crucial for advancing the practical applications of LLMs in critical societal domains. It will enable LLMs to provide reliable, secure, and compliant solutions, enhancing decision-making processes and improving outcomes in finance, healthcare, and law.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe challenges include effectively integrating domain-specific knowledge, securely handling confidential data, processing complex multimodal documents, and ensuring compliance with legal regulations. Naive approaches may fail due to the complexity and sensitivity of the data involved.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has not fully addressed the integration of professional expertise, secure data handling, multimodal data processing, and regulatory compliance in a unified framework. Existing solutions often focus on individual aspects of the problem, lacking a comprehensive approach.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed approach involves developing a unified framework that integrates professional expertise through knowledge graphs, ensures secure data handling using advanced encryption techniques, processes multimodal data using innovative LLM architectures, and incorporates compliance checks. The expected outcomes include a robust LLM capable of providing reliable, secure, and compliant solutions in critical domains.\n"}, {'agent_id': 'agent3', 'result': "Result from the model:### Context Analysis\n\n**Problem Setting:**\nThe introduction discusses the integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains such as finance, healthcare, and law. The focus is on the methodologies, applications, challenges, ethics, and future opportunities of LLMs in these domains. Key challenges include the need for professional expertise, handling of highly confidential data, dealing with extensive multimodal documents, and adhering to high legal risk and strict regulations.\n\n**Prior Approaches:**\n- **Professional Expertise:** The introduction mentions the need for deep knowledge and experience in finance, healthcare, and law, indicating that current LLMs lack the necessary domain-specific expertise.\n- **Confidential Data:** Challenges related to data breaches and secure data handling are highlighted, suggesting that existing methods may not adequately address data privacy concerns.\n- **Multimodal Documents:** The complexity of multimodal data in these domains is noted, implying that current LLMs struggle to interpret and correlate information across different modalities.\n- **Legal Risk and Regulations:** The introduction emphasizes the need for explainability and fairness, indicating that current LLMs may not meet the stringent legal and ethical standards required in these domains.\n\n**Implied Gaps:**\n- **Domain-Specific Expertise:** There is a gap in equipping LLMs with the necessary professional knowledge and experience required for these domains.\n- **Data Privacy:** Existing methods may not provide adequate security for handling highly confidential data.\n- **Multimodal Integration:** Current LLMs lack the capability to effectively interpret and correlate information across different data modalities.\n- **Explainability and Fairness:** There is a need for LLMs to provide explanations and ensure fairness, which is currently lacking.\n\n### Brainstorming\n\n1. **Domain-Specific Knowledge Integration:**\n   - Develop methods to integrate domain-specific knowledge into LLMs, possibly through fine-tuning or knowledge distillation from domain experts.\n\n2. **Secure Data Handling:**\n   - Explore techniques for secure data handling and synthesis to train LLMs on confidential data without compromising privacy.\n\n3. **Multimodal Data Processing:**\n   - Develop innovative architectures and data processing techniques to enable LLMs to interpret and correlate information across different modalities.\n\n4. **Explainability and Fairness:**\n   - Create mechanisms to ensure that LLMs provide explanations for their decisions and adhere to fairness standards.\n\n### Summarization\n\nThe collective ideas revolve around enhancing LLMs to better integrate domain-specific knowledge, handle confidential data securely, process multimodal information effectively, and ensure explainability and fairness. These improvements are crucial for the successful application of LLMs in critical societal domains.\n\n### Formulate a New Research Idea\n\n**High-level summarized insight of a research field:**\nThe integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains such as finance, healthcare, and law presents significant challenges and opportunities. Current LLMs lack the necessary domain-specific expertise, secure data handling capabilities, multimodal data processing techniques, and mechanisms for explainability and fairness.\n\n**Here are the five core questions:**\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nHow can large language models be effectively integrated with critical societal domains (finance, healthcare, law) to address challenges related to domain-specific expertise, data privacy, multimodal data processing, and explainability?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nSolving this problem is crucial for advancing the application of LLMs in critical domains, ensuring that these models can provide reliable, secure, and fair services. This research will have a significant impact on the future of AI in finance, healthcare, and law, potentially leading to improved decision-making and better outcomes for users.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe challenges include equipping LLMs with domain-specific knowledge, ensuring secure data handling, developing effective multimodal data processing techniques, and creating mechanisms for explainability and fairness. These are complex problems that require innovative solutions and interdisciplinary collaboration.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has not fully addressed these challenges due to the complexity of the problems and the need for interdisciplinary collaboration. Additionally, the rapid evolution of LLMs and the specific requirements of critical domains have made it difficult to develop comprehensive solutions.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed approach involves:\n- Developing methods to integrate domain-specific knowledge into LLMs through fine-tuning and knowledge distillation.\n- Exploring secure data handling techniques to train LLMs on confidential data.\n- Creating innovative architectures and data processing techniques for multimodal data processing.\n- Developing mechanisms to ensure explainability and fairness in LLMs.\n\nExpected outcomes include:\n- LLMs that can effectively integrate domain-specific knowledge and handle confidential data securely.\n- Improved multimodal data processing capabilities in LLMs.\n- Enhanced explainability and fairness in LLMs, making them more reliable and trustworthy in critical domains.\n