etal domains.\n\n### Formulate a New Research Idea\n\n**High-level summarized insight:**\nThe integration of large language models (LLMs) with critical societal domains (finance, healthcare, law) presents significant opportunities but also challenges related to knowledge integration, data security, multimodal processing, and explainability.\n\n**Here are the five core questions:**\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nHow can we effectively integrate domain-specific knowledge into LLMs to enhance their performance and reliability in critical societal domains?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nSolving this problem will enable LLMs to provide more accurate and reliable services in finance, healthcare, and law, which are critical for societal function and well-being. It will also advance the field of AI by demonstrating how to bridge the gap between general-purpose models and domain-specific expertise.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nIntegrating domain-specific knowledge into LLMs is challenging due to the need for specialized expertise, the complexity of domain-specific data, and the requirement for models to be both accurate and interpretable. Naive approaches may fail to capture the nuances of domain-specific knowledge or may result in models that are too complex to be practical.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious research has focused on general-purpose LLMs and has not fully addressed the specific challenges of integrating domain-specific knowledge. The complexity of domain-specific data and the need for specialized expertise have been significant barriers. Additionally, there is a lack of standardized methods for integrating domain-specific knowledge into LLMs.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed approach involves developing a framework that integrates domain-specific knowledge into LLMs using knowledge graphs and ontologies. The framework 