aw.\\n   - **Evaluating Performance, Explainability, and Fairness:** Use defined metrics to assess performance, explainability, and fairness.\\n\\n4. **Refine Methodology:**\\n   - **Architecture of the GNN-based Knowledge Graph:** Design a GNN architecture for multimodal data and complex relationships.\\n   - **Method for Aligning Knowledge Graphs:** Develop a method to align GNN\'s knowledge graph with LLM\'s internal representations.\\n   - **Process for Training and Fine-tuning LLMs:** Implement a training and fine-tuning process leveraging the GNN-based knowledge graph.\\n\\n5. **Address Technical Challenges:**\\n   - **Handling Multimodal Data:** Use multimodal fusion techniques.\\n   - **Ensuring Data Security:** Implement homomorphic encryption and differential privacy.\\n   - **Improving Explainability and Fairness:** Develop methods to enhance explainability and ensure fairness.\\n\\n#### Deliverable\\n- A refined research proposal with detailed technical components, datasets, evaluation metrics, and a plan for preliminary experiments.\\n\\n#### High-level Summarized Insight\\nGraph Neural Networks (GNNs) can enhance Large Language Models (LLMs) in critical domains (finance, healthcare, law) by integrating domain-specific knowledge, handling secure data, processing multimodal information, and ensuring explainability and fairness.\\n\\n#### Core Questions Addressed\\n1. **What is the problem?** Integrating domain-specific knowledge into LLMs to enhance performance in critical domains.\\n2. **Why is it interesting and important?** Enables informed decisions, improving reliability and effectiveness in high-stakes domains.\\n3. **Why is it hard?** Complexity and diversity of domain-specific information, ensuring performance and efficiency.\\n4. **Why hasn\'t it been solved before?** Lack of exploration into GNNs for this purpose, complexity of the problem.\\n5. **What are the key components of the approach and results?** Datasets, evaluation metrics, preliminary experiments, methodology, technical challenges.\\n\\n#### Expected Outcomes\\n- Improved performance of LLMs in critical domains.\\n- Enhanced explainability and fairness of LLMs.\\n- A robust framework for integrating domain-specific knowledge into LLMs using GNNs.\\n\\nThis refined research proposal provides a comprehensive roadmap for addressing technical challenges and achieving the research objectives."}'}], 'summary': '```json\n{\n  "[Question 1] - What is the problem?": "How can large language models (LLMs) be effectively integrated with domain-specific knowledge in critical societal domains (finance, healthcare, law) while ensuring data security, multimodal data processing, and ethical compliance?",\n\n  "[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?": "Solving this problem will enable LLMs to be more robust and reliable in critical domains, leading to improved decision-making and better outcomes. This research will advance the state of the art in LLMs and contribute to the development of more trustworthy AI systems, ensuring they can be safely and ethically deployed in high-stakes environments. It will also facilitate the integration of LLMs with professional expertise, enhancing their capabilities and applicability across diverse fields.",\n\n  "[Question 3] - Why is it hard?": "The challenges include equipping LLMs with the necessary domain-specific knowledge, ensuring secure handling of highly confidential data, developing methods to process and correlate multimodal data, and addressing ethical concerns related to explainability and fairness. Naive approaches may fail due to the complexity of these domains and the need for specialized techniques. Technical obstacles include data privacy, model interpretability, and the integration of diverse data types. Theoretical challenges involve understanding the limitations of current LLM architectures and developing new methods to overcome them.",\n\n  "[Question 4] - Why hasn\'t it been solved before?": 